{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"38a66483-1d17-4db1-9618-cea330550c85","content":"\n\nTo switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Delete this line or set to false -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n\n2. That's it — **MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform** when `UseVSTest` is not set to `true`.\n\n**Key behavior changes to be aware of:**\n\n- Run tests with `dotnet test` as before (works with SDK ≥ 3.8).\n- You can also run the test executable directly (`./YourTests.exe`).\n- CLI options differ slightly (e.g., `--filter` becomes `--treenode-filter`; use `dotnet test --help` to see new options).\n- Some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` entries may need updating.\n- Extensions like code coverage or loggers now use the new platform's extension model — check that any third-party adapters you use support Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"792af6f2-0115-4c9d-ac1f-29dcf745900c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration, not a code change request for a specific repository.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":343},"id":"229f9553-ea8d-4127-ba38-a1a411953af7","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:47:38.370Z","parentId":"938d7887-8eff-4a02-9ef5-b1ddc0fb0d0c"}
